<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}+{7}{y}=-{37}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+{6}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},-{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --3. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{3}}{{1}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{3}}}{{1}}{\left({1}{x}+{7}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{3}}}{{1}}{\left(-{37}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{3}\right)}{x}+{21}{y}=-{111}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+{6}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{27}{y}=-{135}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{135}}{{27}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+{7}{\left(-{5}\right)}=-{37}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+{\left(-{35}\right)}=-{37}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}=-{37}-{\left(-{35}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}=-{2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{2}}{{1}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},-{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

